1. How can employees show their managers that they are trustworthy?
Solution : A. Deliver projects on time and communicate if anything is off track

2. You are constantly looking for ways to improve and stay in step with your manager. What is one way you can check in on your biggest growth areas?
Solution : B. Communicate frequently about where you can improve

3. Both you and your manager have suggested approaches to solving a customer's problem. Which of the following actions can nudge your manager toward your solution?
Solution : D. Show how what you want to do advances your boss's goals
